      </div>

      <div class="prose">
        <h3>Market Trends Affecting 2026 Decision</h3>

        <p>Several 2026 market trends impact the commercial versus residential decision:</p>

        <p><strong>Energy Efficiency Incentives:</strong> Federal and state programs are driving commercial building retrofits, creating a $12 billion market opportunity through 2028. Residential incentives focus on heat pump installations, expanding that market by 35% annually.</p>

        <p><strong>Labor Shortage Impact:</strong> The HVAC technician shortage affects both markets differently. Commercial work requires more specialized skills, making qualified technicians harder to find but commanding higher wages ($65,000-$85,000 vs $45,000-$65,000 residential).</p>

        <p><strong>Technology Adoption:</strong> Smart building integration creates ongoing commercial opportunities, while residential customers increasingly expect connected thermostats and monitoring systems.</p>

        <p>Understanding these trends helps position your business for long-term growth regardless of your chosen focus.</p>
      </div>
